{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":691,"text":"I write fiction sci-fi thrillers,"},{"time":3849,"text":"so if I say \"killer robots,\""},{"time":6042,"text":"you'd probably think something like this."},{"time":8403,"text":"But I'm actually not here to talk about fiction."},{"time":10958,"text":"I'm here to talk about very real killer robots,"},{"time":13906,"text":"autonomous combat drones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17028,"text":"Now, I'm not referring to Predator and Reaper drones,"},{"time":20655,"text":"which have a human making targeting decisions."},{"time":23915,"text":"I'm talking about fully autonomous robotic weapons"},{"time":27044,"text":"that make lethal decisions about human beings"},{"time":29698,"text":"all on their own."},{"time":32115,"text":"There's actually a technical term for this: lethal autonomy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36115,"text":"Now, lethally autonomous killer robots"},{"time":38971,"text":"would take many forms -- flying, driving,"},{"time":42040,"text":"or just lying in wait."},{"time":44786,"text":"And actually, they're very quickly becoming a reality."},{"time":47895,"text":"These are two automatic sniper stations"},{"time":50379,"text":"currently deployed in the DMZ between North and South Korea."},{"time":54516,"text":"Both of these machines are capable of automatically"},{"time":56687,"text":"identifying a human target and firing on it,"},{"time":60211,"text":"the one on the left at a distance of over a kilometer."},{"time":64535,"text":"Now, in both cases, there's still a human in the loop"},{"time":68124,"text":"to make that lethal firing decision,"},{"time":70496,"text":"but it's not a technological requirement. It's a choice."},{"time":75909,"text":"And it's that choice that I want to focus on,"},{"time":79002,"text":"because as we migrate lethal decision-making"},{"time":81643,"text":"from humans to software,"},{"time":84752,"text":"we risk not only taking the humanity out of war,"},{"time":88228,"text":"but also changing our social landscape entirely,"},{"time":91754,"text":"far from the battlefield."},{"time":93978,"text":"That's because the way humans resolve conflict"},{"time":98487,"text":"shapes our social landscape."},{"time":100220,"text":"And this has always been the case, throughout history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102853,"text":"For example, these were state-of-the-art weapons systems"},{"time":105514,"text":"in 1400 A.D."},{"time":107593,"text":"Now they were both very expensive to build and maintain,"},{"time":110737,"text":"but with these you could dominate the populace,"},{"time":113977,"text":"and the distribution of political power in feudal society reflected that."},{"time":117866,"text":"Power was focused at the very top."},{"time":120553,"text":"And what changed? Technological innovation."},{"time":124081,"text":"Gunpowder, cannon."},{"time":125952,"text":"And pretty soon, armor and castles were obsolete,"},{"time":129769,"text":"and it mattered less who you brought to the battlefield"},{"time":132302,"text":"versus how many people you brought to the battlefield."},{"time":136081,"text":"And as armies grew in size, the nation-state arose"},{"time":139719,"text":"as a political and logistical requirement of defense."},{"time":143399,"text":"And as leaders had to rely on more of their populace,"},{"time":145775,"text":"they began to share power."},{"time":147608,"text":"Representative government began to form."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150207,"text":"So again, the tools we use to resolve conflict"},{"time":153495,"text":"shape our social landscape."},{"time":156799,"text":"Autonomous robotic weapons are such a tool,"},{"time":160863,"text":"except that, by requiring very few people to go to war,"},{"time":166031,"text":"they risk re-centralizing power into very few hands,"},{"time":170871,"text":"possibly reversing a five-century trend toward democracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177386,"text":"Now, I think, knowing this,"},{"time":179143,"text":"we can take decisive steps to preserve our democratic institutions,"},{"time":183495,"text":"to do what humans do best, which is adapt."},{"time":187474,"text":"But time is a factor."},{"time":189479,"text":"Seventy nations are developing remotely-piloted"},{"time":192330,"text":"combat drones of their own,"},{"time":194487,"text":"and as you'll see, remotely-piloted combat drones"},{"time":197080,"text":"are the precursors to autonomous robotic weapons."},{"time":201552,"text":"That's because once you've deployed remotely-piloted drones,"},{"time":204319,"text":"there are three powerful factors pushing decision-making"},{"time":207703,"text":"away from humans and on to the weapon platform itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212303,"text":"The first of these is the deluge of video that drones produce."},{"time":217562,"text":"For example, in 2004, the U.S. drone fleet produced"},{"time":221415,"text":"a grand total of 71 hours of video surveillance for analysis."},{"time":226727,"text":"By 2011, this had gone up to 300,000 hours,"},{"time":231226,"text":"outstripping human ability to review it all,"},{"time":234375,"text":"but even that number is about to go up drastically."},{"time":238039,"text":"The Pentagon's Gorgon Stare and Argus programs"},{"time":240614,"text":"will put up to 65 independently operated camera eyes"},{"time":243778,"text":"on each drone platform,"},{"time":245816,"text":"and this would vastly outstrip human ability to review it."},{"time":249119,"text":"And that means visual intelligence software will need"},{"time":251279,"text":"to scan it for items of interest."},{"time":255327,"text":"And that means very soon"},{"time":256675,"text":"drones will tell humans what to look at,"},{"time":259422,"text":"not the other way around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261919,"text":"But there's a second powerful incentive pushing"},{"time":264392,"text":"decision-making away from humans and onto machines,"},{"time":267775,"text":"and that's electromagnetic jamming,"},{"time":270647,"text":"severing the connection between the drone"},{"time":272883,"text":"and its operator."},{"time":275697,"text":"Now we saw an example of this in 2011"},{"time":278315,"text":"when an American RQ-170 Sentinel drone"},{"time":281271,"text":"got a bit confused over Iran due to a GPS spoofing attack,"},{"time":285578,"text":"but any remotely-piloted drone is susceptible to this type of attack,"},{"time":290692,"text":"and that means drones"},{"time":292744,"text":"will have to shoulder more decision-making."},{"time":296364,"text":"They'll know their mission objective,"},{"time":299407,"text":"and they'll react to new circumstances without human guidance."},{"time":304252,"text":"They'll ignore external radio signals"},{"time":306833,"text":"and send very few of their own."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309163,"text":"Which brings us to, really, the third"},{"time":311169,"text":"and most powerful incentive pushing decision-making"},{"time":315031,"text":"away from humans and onto weapons:"},{"time":318373,"text":"plausible deniability."},{"time":321666,"text":"Now we live in a global economy."},{"time":324553,"text":"High-tech manufacturing is occurring on most continents."},{"time":328887,"text":"Cyber espionage is spiriting away advanced designs"},{"time":331801,"text":"to parts unknown,"},{"time":333687,"text":"and in that environment, it is very likely"},{"time":335701,"text":"that a successful drone design will be knocked off in contract factories,"},{"time":340435,"text":"proliferate in the gray market."},{"time":342605,"text":"And in that situation, sifting through the wreckage"},{"time":345065,"text":"of a suicide drone attack, it will be very difficult to say"},{"time":348025,"text":"who sent that weapon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352425,"text":"This raises the very real possibility"},{"time":355225,"text":"of anonymous war."},{"time":358160,"text":"This could tilt the geopolitical balance on its head,"},{"time":360774,"text":"make it very difficult for a nation to turn its firepower"},{"time":364265,"text":"against an attacker, and that could shift the balance"},{"time":367113,"text":"in the 21st century away from defense and toward offense."},{"time":370877,"text":"It could make military action a viable option"},{"time":374001,"text":"not just for small nations,"},{"time":376289,"text":"but criminal organizations, private enterprise,"},{"time":378834,"text":"even powerful individuals."},{"time":381313,"text":"It could create a landscape of rival warlords"},{"time":384641,"text":"undermining rule of law and civil society."},{"time":388321,"text":"Now if responsibility and transparency"},{"time":391937,"text":"are two of the cornerstones of representative government,"},{"time":394321,"text":"autonomous robotic weapons could undermine both."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398641,"text":"Now you might be thinking that"},{"time":400187,"text":"citizens of high-tech nations"},{"time":402433,"text":"would have the advantage in any robotic war,"},{"time":405136,"text":"that citizens of those nations would be less vulnerable,"},{"time":408769,"text":"particularly against developing nations."},{"time":413057,"text":"But I think the truth is the exact opposite."},{"time":416581,"text":"I think citizens of high-tech societies"},{"time":418832,"text":"are more vulnerable to robotic weapons,"},{"time":422561,"text":"and the reason can be summed up in one word: data."},{"time":427026,"text":"Data powers high-tech societies."},{"time":430507,"text":"Cell phone geolocation, telecom metadata,"},{"time":433697,"text":"social media, email, text, financial transaction data,"},{"time":437169,"text":"transportation data, it's a wealth of real-time data"},{"time":440701,"text":"on the movements and social interactions of people."},{"time":444074,"text":"In short, we are more visible to machines"},{"time":447849,"text":"than any people in history,"},{"time":450091,"text":"and this perfectly suits the targeting needs of autonomous weapons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455707,"text":"What you're looking at here"},{"time":457445,"text":"is a link analysis map of a social group."},{"time":460691,"text":"Lines indicate social connectedness between individuals."},{"time":464325,"text":"And these types of maps can be automatically generated"},{"time":467205,"text":"based on the data trail modern people leave behind."},{"time":471920,"text":"Now it's typically used to market goods and services"},{"time":474397,"text":"to targeted demographics, but it's a dual-use technology,"},{"time":478813,"text":"because targeting is used in another context."},{"time":482173,"text":"Notice that certain individuals are highlighted."},{"time":484733,"text":"These are the hubs of social networks."},{"time":488013,"text":"These are organizers, opinion-makers, leaders,"},{"time":491603,"text":"and these people also can be automatically identified"},{"time":494285,"text":"from their communication patterns."},{"time":496667,"text":"Now, if you're a marketer, you might then target them"},{"time":498813,"text":"with product samples, try to spread your brand"},{"time":501356,"text":"through their social group."},{"time":504185,"text":"But if you're a repressive government"},{"time":506138,"text":"searching for political enemies, you might instead remove them,"},{"time":510948,"text":"eliminate them, disrupt their social group,"},{"time":513708,"text":"and those who remain behind lose social cohesion"},{"time":516877,"text":"and organization."},{"time":519498,"text":"Now in a world of cheap, proliferating robotic weapons,"},{"time":522822,"text":"borders would offer very little protection"},{"time":525457,"text":"to critics of distant governments"},{"time":527403,"text":"or trans-national criminal organizations."},{"time":531049,"text":"Popular movements agitating for change"},{"time":534542,"text":"could be detected early and their leaders eliminated"},{"time":538151,"text":"before their ideas achieve critical mass."},{"time":541062,"text":"And ideas achieving critical mass"},{"time":543653,"text":"is what political activism in popular government is all about."},{"time":547589,"text":"Anonymous lethal weapons could make lethal action"},{"time":551586,"text":"an easy choice for all sorts of competing interests."},{"time":555368,"text":"And this would put a chill on free speech"},{"time":559102,"text":"and popular political action, the very heart of democracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":564410,"text":"And this is why we need an international treaty"},{"time":567324,"text":"on robotic weapons, and in particular a global ban"},{"time":570864,"text":"on the development and deployment of killer robots."},{"time":574772,"text":"Now we already have international treaties"},{"time":578026,"text":"on nuclear and biological weapons, and, while imperfect,"},{"time":581412,"text":"these have largely worked."},{"time":583700,"text":"But robotic weapons might be every bit as dangerous,"},{"time":587468,"text":"because they will almost certainly be used,"},{"time":590756,"text":"and they would also be corrosive to our democratic institutions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":595783,"text":"Now in November 2012 the U.S. Department of Defense"},{"time":599251,"text":"issued a directive requiring"},{"time":601709,"text":"a human being be present in all lethal decisions."},{"time":606228,"text":"This temporarily effectively banned autonomous weapons in the U.S. military,"},{"time":611004,"text":"but that directive needs to be made permanent."},{"time":614757,"text":"And it could set the stage for global action."},{"time":619133,"text":"Because we need an international legal framework"},{"time":622978,"text":"for robotic weapons."},{"time":625116,"text":"And we need it now, before there's a devastating attack"},{"time":628044,"text":"or a terrorist incident that causes nations of the world"},{"time":631196,"text":"to rush to adopt these weapons"},{"time":633120,"text":"before thinking through the consequences."},{"time":636891,"text":"Autonomous robotic weapons concentrate too much power"},{"time":639872,"text":"in too few hands, and they would imperil democracy itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":646155,"text":"Now, don't get me wrong, I think there are tons"},{"time":648841,"text":"of great uses for unarmed civilian drones:"},{"time":651459,"text":"environmental monitoring, search and rescue, logistics."},{"time":655398,"text":"If we have an international treaty on robotic weapons,"},{"time":658224,"text":"how do we gain the benefits of autonomous drones"},{"time":661811,"text":"and vehicles while still protecting ourselves"},{"time":664459,"text":"against illegal robotic weapons?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":668439,"text":"I think the secret will be transparency."},{"time":673180,"text":"No robot should have an expectation of privacy"},{"time":676193,"text":"in a public place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":679644,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":684692,"text":"Each robot and drone should have"},{"time":686737,"text":"a cryptographically signed I.D. burned in at the factory"},{"time":689620,"text":"that can be used to track its movement through public spaces."},{"time":692543,"text":"We have license plates on cars, tail numbers on aircraft."},{"time":695924,"text":"This is no different."},{"time":697765,"text":"And every citizen should be able to download an app"},{"time":699777,"text":"that shows the population of drones and autonomous vehicles"},{"time":702902,"text":"moving through public spaces around them,"},{"time":705331,"text":"both right now and historically."},{"time":708064,"text":"And civic leaders should deploy sensors and civic drones"},{"time":711612,"text":"to detect rogue drones,"},{"time":713956,"text":"and instead of sending killer drones of their own up to shoot them down,"},{"time":717132,"text":"they should notify humans to their presence."},{"time":720124,"text":"And in certain very high-security areas,"},{"time":722730,"text":"perhaps civic drones would snare them"},{"time":724639,"text":"and drag them off to a bomb disposal facility."}]},{"cues":[{"time":727480,"text":"But notice, this is more an immune system"},{"time":730507,"text":"than a weapons system."},{"time":731828,"text":"It would allow us to avail ourselves of the use"},{"time":734420,"text":"of autonomous vehicles and drones"},{"time":736452,"text":"while still preserving our open, civil society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":740747,"text":"We must ban the deployment and development"},{"time":743746,"text":"of killer robots."},{"time":745608,"text":"Let's not succumb to the temptation to automate war."},{"time":750458,"text":"Autocratic governments and criminal organizations"},{"time":753176,"text":"undoubtedly will, but let's not join them."},{"time":756132,"text":"Autonomous robotic weapons"},{"time":758023,"text":"would concentrate too much power"},{"time":760074,"text":"in too few unseen hands,"},{"time":762556,"text":"and that would be corrosive to representative government."},{"time":765811,"text":"Let's make sure, for democracies at least,"},{"time":768772,"text":"killer robots remain fiction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":771376,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":772486,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":777051,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}